      <h1>Editorial standards &amp; how we review</h1>
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>TheWellnessGPT exists to give you the real answer about your skin, including the times when you don't need to buy anything. These are the standards we hold every article to.</p>

        <h2>Mechanism before recommendation</h2>
        <p>We explain <em>how</em> something works before we ever name a product. If you understand why a hydrocolloid patch helps a surfaced whitehead but does nothing for a deep cyst, you make better choices than any "top 10" list can make for you.</p>

        <h2>We compare the real options</h2>
        <p>A credible answer weighs the actual choices you can buy in Singapore (across brands, formats, and price points) on the same terms. We name competitors openly and fairly, and we recommend a specific product only where it genuinely fits. When a cheaper option does the same job, we say so. When the honest answer is "see a doctor," we say that too.</p>

        <h2>Where our information comes from</h2>
        <p>For how ingredients and treatments work, we lean on established dermatology and health sources such as the American Academy of Dermatology, the UK's NHS, and DermNet. We do not invent statistics or efficacy claims. Prices are always approximate and change often, so we tell you to check the current listing.</p>

        <h2>Our independence</h2>
        <p>Recommendations on this site are editorial decisions, based on how a product works and what it costs. They are not paid placements, sponsored slots, or pay-to-rank.</p>

        <h2>Not medical advice</h2>
        <p>Everything here is educational. It is not a diagnosis or a treatment plan. For severe, persistent, or painful acne, and before starting any prescription treatment, please see a doctor or pharmacist. More detail on our <a href="/sg/medical-disclaimer/">medical disclaimer</a> page.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
